---
// HeroModality — the homepage centerpiece. One epistemic sentence carries the
// whole program: the modal word "must" is the object of study, the fork below it
// is the theoretical question the thesis adjudicates (Kratzer's set of possible
// worlds vs. Lassiter's degree of certainty), and the two testbeds are where a
// single prediction is read off at once — the human mind and a language model.
// Pure CSS, no JS. Accent: --accent-deep-purple (modality) throughout.
---

<figure
  class="hero-mod"
  aria-label="The sentence “It must be raining.” The modal word must is the object of study. Two competing analyses of modal force — Kratzer's quantification over possible worlds and Lassiter's degree of certainty — are tested in two systems, the human mind and a language model."
>
  <p class="hero-mod-sent">
    <span class="hm-quote hm-quote-open" aria-hidden="true">“</span>It
    <a class="hm-word" href="/research/modus" aria-label="must — the modal, the MODUS thesis">
      <span class="hm-word-text">must</span>
      <span class="hm-tip" aria-hidden="true">
        <span class="hm-tip-cat">Modal force</span>
        <span class="hm-tip-name">MODUS · the thesis</span>
        <span class="hm-tip-q">Is <em>must</em> a set of possible worlds, or a degree of certainty? And does a model represent it, or only ride the word?</span>
      </span>
    </a>
    be raining.<span class="hm-quote hm-quote-close" aria-hidden="true">”</span>
  </p>

  <p class="hm-fork-q">What is that <em>must</em> made of?</p>
  <div class="hm-fork">
    <div class="hm-read">
      <span class="hm-glyph" aria-hidden="true">◇ □</span>
      <span class="hm-read-body">
        <span class="hm-read-who">Kratzer</span>
        <span class="hm-read-what">a set of possible worlds, quantified</span>
      </span>
    </div>
    <span class="hm-vs" aria-hidden="true">vs</span>
    <div class="hm-read">
      <span class="hm-glyph hm-gauge" aria-hidden="true">
        <span class="hm-gauge-fill"></span>
      </span>
      <span class="hm-read-body">
        <span class="hm-read-who">Lassiter</span>
        <span class="hm-read-what">a single degree of certainty</span>
      </span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="hm-systems">
    <span class="hm-systems-lead">One prediction, read in two systems</span>
    <span class="hm-systems-row">
      <span class="hm-sys">the human mind</span>
      <span class="hm-sys-amp" aria-hidden="true">&amp;</span>
      <span class="hm-sys">a language model</span>
    </span>
  </div>

  <figcaption class="hero-mod-cap">One modal, two theories, two systems. Hover <em>must</em>, or click to open the thesis.</figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .hero-mod { margin: 0; padding: 0; max-width: 32rem; }

  .hero-mod-sent {
    font-family: var(--font-display, serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.7rem, 1.2rem + 2vw, 2.35rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0 0 1.9rem;
  }

  /* big decorative quotes framing the example */
  .hm-quote {
    font-family: var(--font-display, Georgia, serif);
    font-size: 2.4em;
    line-height: 0;
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-text-dim) 55%, transparent);
  }
  .hm-quote-open { margin-right: 0.04em; vertical-align: -0.42em; }
  .hm-quote-close { margin-left: 0.03em; vertical-align: -0.42em; }

  .hm-word {
    position: relative;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent-deep-purple);
    border-radius: 5px;
    padding: 1px 5px;
    transition: background 0.14s ease;
  }
  .hm-word:focus-visible { outline: none; }
  .hm-word:hover,
  .hm-word:focus-visible {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-deep-purple) 15%, transparent);
  }

  /* the bubble preview on `must` */
  .hm-tip {
    position: absolute;
    top: calc(100% + 11px);
    left: 0;
    width: max-content;
    max-width: min(300px, 78vw);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 10px 28px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.11);
    padding: 0.8rem 0.95rem;
    opacity: 0;
    visibility: hidden;
    transform: translateY(-5px);
    transition: opacity 0.16s ease, transform 0.16s ease, visibility 0.16s;
    z-index: 5;
    font-family: var(--font-sans, sans-serif);
  }
  .hm-word:hover .hm-tip,
  .hm-word:focus-within .hm-tip {
    opacity: 1;
    visibility: visible;
    transform: translateY(0);
  }
  .hm-tip::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 100%;
    left: 22px;
    border: 6px solid transparent;
    border-bottom-color: var(--color-border);
  }
  .hm-tip-cat {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.13em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent-deep-purple);
    margin: 0 0 4px;
  }
  .hm-tip-name { display: block; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text); margin: 0 0 5px; }
  .hm-tip-q { display: block; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--color-text-muted); }
  .hm-tip-q em { font-style: italic; }

  /* the theory fork */
  .hm-fork-q {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.13em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
  }
  .hm-fork-q em { font-style: normal; color: var(--accent-deep-purple); }

  .hm-fork {
    display: flex;
    align-items: stretch;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .hm-read {
    flex: 1 1 12rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.7rem;
    padding: 0.7rem 0.85rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-deep-purple) 4%, transparent);
  }
  .hm-vs {
    align-self: center;
    font-family: var(--font-display, serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
  }
  .hm-glyph {
    flex: none;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 2.1rem;
    height: 2.1rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--accent-deep-purple);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-deep-purple) 12%, transparent);
  }
  /* a tiny "certainty gauge" for the degree reading */
  .hm-gauge { position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
  .hm-gauge-fill {
    position: absolute;
    left: 0; bottom: 0;
    width: 100%; height: 68%;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-deep-purple) 42%, transparent);
  }
  .hm-read-body { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2px; min-width: 0; }
  .hm-read-who {
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .hm-read-what {
    font-size: 12.5px;
    line-height: 1.35;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  /* the two testbeds */
  .hm-systems {
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
    padding-top: 1.1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .hm-systems-lead {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.13em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
  }
  .hm-systems-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.7rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .hm-sys {
    font-family: var(--font-display, serif);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-deep-purple) 32%, var(--color-border));
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-deep-purple) 5%, transparent);
  }
  .hm-sys-amp { font-family: var(--font-display, serif); font-style: italic; color: var(--color-text-dim); }

  .hero-mod-cap {
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
    font-size: 11.5px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
  }
  .hero-mod-cap em { font-style: normal; color: var(--accent-deep-purple); font-weight: 600; }
</style>
